\LosItem{$\Z/n\Z$}%


////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////


The set of integers modulo $n$:
$\Z/n\Z = \left\{0, 1, 2, 3, \ldots, n - 1\right\}$.
This is the set of all possible remainders of integers after
division by $n$.  Addition and multiplication are defined in the
usual way, with the proviso that multiples of $n$ are thrown away.
For example, in $\Z/5\Z$ we have $2 + 4 = 1$ and $2 \times 4 = 3$.


